import networkx as nx
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import osmnx as ox

Function for degree distribution¶

In [2]:
def degree_centrality(G):
    vk = dict(G.degree())
    vk = list(vk.values())
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    plt.hist(vk, density=True)
    plt.title("Distribution of the Degree Centrality", fontsize=20)
    plt.ylabel("P(k)", fontsize=20)
    plt.xlabel("Degree Centrality (k)", fontsize=20)
    plt.show(True)

def closeness_centrality(G):
    CLC = dict(nx.closeness_centrality(G))
    CLC = list(CLC.values())
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    plt.hist(CLC, density=True)
    plt.title("Distribution of the Closeness Centrality", fontsize=20)
    plt.ylabel("P(CLC)", fontsize=20)
    plt.xlabel("Closeness Centrality (CLC)", fontsize=20)
    plt.show(True)

def betweenness_centrality(G):
    B = dict(nx.betweenness_centrality(G))
    B = list(B.values())
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    plt.hist(B, density=True)
    plt.title("Distribution of the betweenness centrality", fontsize=20)
    plt.ylabel("P(B)", fontsize=20)
    plt.xlabel("Betweenness centrality (B)", fontsize=20)
    plt.show(True)

Piedmont network¶

In [3]:
Gx = ox.graph_from_place('Piedmont, California, USA', network_type='drive')
Gx_projected = ox.project_graph(Gx)
fig, ax = ox.plot_graph(Gx_projected)
G = Gx.to_undirected()
Gcc=sorted(nx.connected_component_subgraphs(G), key = len, reverse=True)
G=Gcc[0]
G = nx.convert_node_labels_to_integers(G, first_label=0)

In [ ]:

The Degree Centrality is very similar between all cities which is expected since they are mostly urban and well connected. However, when we compare the Betweenness Centrality and the Closeness Centrality, we can see that Piedmont certainly is the easier city to navigate, because these measures have higher values than So Carlos, Paris or Melbourne. The Closeness Centrality indicates that the nodes (places in the city) are closer together in Piedmont and the Betweenness Centrality indicates that it is more likely to pass trough a certain place when walking in the city. This result is expected since Piedmont is smaller than the other cities. ¶
